    <summary>Newt — the site and network connector for Pangolin (WireGuard-based zero-trust remote access)</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[Newt is the official site and network connector for Pangolin, an identity-aware, self-hostable tunneled reverse proxy and mesh VPN built on WireGuard. It runs on a machine inside a private network and opens an outbound WireGuard tunnel to a Pangolin server, exposing local sites and services for zero-trust remote access without inbound firewall ports.

### Features
- Outbound WireGuard tunnel to a Pangolin server (no inbound ports required)
- Exposes local sites and services for zero-trust (ZTNA) remote access
- Optional Windows service ("Newt WireGuard Tunnel Service") for unattended operation
- `newt` command available on the PATH

### What this package does
- Installs the official Windows `newt` binary
- Optionally registers and starts the Newt Windows service when connection parameters are supplied: `choco install pangolin.newt --params "/Id:SITE_ID /Secret:SECRET /Endpoint:https://PANGOLIN_HOST"`
- Suitable for unattended/automated deployments with Chocolatey

### Compatibility and requirements
- Windows 10/11 (per upstream support)
- Administrator privileges may be required

### Verification after installation
- Run `newt status`, or check the "Newt WireGuard Tunnel Service" in services.msc when installed as a service

### Disclaimer
This Chocolatey package is community-maintained and is not created, endorsed, or supported by Fossorial, Inc.

